                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d595">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.6363 Standard Oil/433: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-12-12T15:00:00+03:25"
                            >December 12, 1940—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 12—2:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>269. Legation’s 264, December 4. Anderson left Tehran today. Acting Foreign
                    Minister told Engert that the Iranian Government feared acceptance of his
                    proposal might create apprehension in Soviet and Axis circles and draw attention
                    to the oil question which Iran wished to avoid.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
